sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M30100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is my refactoring of a section of the M13K07 phage genome for 20.109.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dawn Spelke
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Refactored to make phage more conducive to future engineering attempts, as well as to attempt some more interesting modifications.
